# Static site guidelines

When editing frontend files in this project:

## HTML

- Use semantic elements (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `article`, `section`, `footer`)
- Include `lang` on `<html>`, viewport meta, and descriptive `<title>` / meta description
- Add `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` on navigation and interactive regions
- Keep sample blog content in `index.html` unless splitting into separate pages is requested

## CSS

- Use CSS custom properties for colors, spacing, and typography tokens
- Mobile-first responsive layout; test at narrow and wide breakpoints
- Fonts: Inter (body/UI), Playfair Display (headings/editorial accents)
- Prefer class-based styling; avoid inline styles

## JavaScript

- Use vanilla JS only — no frameworks or bundlers
- Wire up mobile nav toggle, post/topic filtering, and newsletter form in `script.js`
- Use `addEventListener`; avoid inline `onclick` handlers
- Guard DOM queries and handle missing elements gracefully

## Do not

- Introduce React, Vue, or other SPA frameworks without explicit approval
- Add heavy dependencies or a build pipeline for simple UI changes
- Break GitHub Pages deployment (paths must work as static files from repo root)
